Workers Compensation Rating Procedure

A rating is a risk-based calculation of a premium based on a set of input characteristics. We use rating procedures to price insurance products and health plans.

Integration Procedure for Workers Compensation

To rate the Workers Compensation insurance product, we use this Integration procedure:

Type/Subtype - insRating/WorkersCompensationNCCi
Integration Procedure Name - WorkersCompensationNCCIRating

Here are details of what each component in the Integration Procedure does:
RatePayrollLinesAction: Calculates the payroll using PricingMatrixCalculationService
addLocationInstanceKeyForSingle: Sets the premium for a single input
MultipleInputsNoMerge: Sets different premiums for multiple inputs
SingleInputDoMerge: Merges results for a single input
RollUpCoverageAmounts: Sets the sum of all coverage amounts
MergeInputsForCoverageB: Arranges Coverage B values in order
MergeInputs: Arranges all inputs in an order
RateCoverageBAndFinal: Calculates liability and schedule using PricingMatrixCalculationService
MergeRatingResults: Merges coverage premiums for different locations
MergeInProductKeys: Merges product keys for different locations
transformOptionalPremium: Transforms data for optional premiums
SetOutput: Arranges output premium values in an order

The Workers Compensation rating procedure also uses calculation procedures to perform calculations on matrix lookups and user-defined variables and constants.
